var storyContent = ﻿{"inkVersion":20,"root":[[{"->":"1Prologue"},["done",{"#f":5,"#n":"g-0"}],null],"done",{"1Prologue":[["^Clark lays in bed, tossing and turning. It wasn't the faint musty smell of the room that kept him awake. There was something vaguely unsettling in his mind about the odd will, but the sheer amount made it impossible for him to refuse the strange offer.","\n",["ev",{"^->":"1Prologue.0.2.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-0","flg":18},{"s":["^Begin to recall the events of the last few days.",{"->":"$r","var":true},null]}],{"c-0":["ev",{"^->":"1Prologue.0.c-0.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.2.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n",{"->":"11Countryhouse"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"11Countryhouse":[["^\"So you're one of the beneficiaries of the will, Auntie?\"","\n","^\"Yes, it's so nice to receive such a large sum of money out of the blue.\"","\n",["ev",{"^->":"11Countryhouse.0.4.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-0","flg":18},{"s":["^\"But who exactly is Mr. Marshall, and why have I never heard of him?\"",{"->":"$r","var":true},null]}],{"c-0":["ev",{"^->":"11Countryhouse.0.c-0.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.4.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n",{"->":"Whos_is_Marshall"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"Whos_is_Marshall":[["^\"I hadn't actually heard of him, I heard from my lawyer that he was a distant relative of ours, and that we were the only few legal heirs to his estate.\"","\n",["ev",{"^->":"Whos_is_Marshall.0.2.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-0","flg":18},{"s":["^\"It was nice to get such a large sum of money while I was unemployed.\"",{"->":"$r","var":true},null]}],{"c-0":["ev",{"^->":"Whos_is_Marshall.0.c-0.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.2.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n",{"->":"Other_relatives"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"Other_relatives":[["^\"Yeah, I heard from your parents that you've just been fired by your boss. Even with five people splitting that inheritance, it is still a lot of money.\"","\n",["ev",{"^->":"Other_relatives.0.2.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-0","flg":18},{"s":["^\"Five people?\"",{"->":"$r","var":true},null]}],{"c-0":["ev",{"^->":"Other_relatives.0.c-0.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.2.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n",{"->":"Five_people"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"Five_people":[["^\"In addition to the two of us, there is a couple who will get the property, as well as the lawyer in charge of the distribution of the estate, who is also a friend of Mr. Marshall's.\"","\n","ev","str","^Drive to Mr. Marshall's house","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"meet_other"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"meet_other":[["^Clark and Aunt Penny arrived at their destination. A huge old house built with its back to the forest, the old iron gates slowly being pushed open by the butler. The gardens were decorated with huge marble statues and old fountains that alluded to the wealth of the previous owners.","\n",["ev",{"^->":"meet_other.0.2.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-0","flg":18},{"s":["^The housekeeper was waiting for them in the front room, \"Welcome, please do so in the drawing room, the others are already here and the lawyer will announce the details of the will\"",{"->":"$r","var":true},null]}],{"c-0":["ev",{"^->":"meet_other.0.c-0.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.2.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n",{"->":"12Inheritance"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"12Inheritance":[["^Clark entered the old mansion and the living room was nowhere near as luxurious as Clark had expected. It was covered with various decorations, small sculptures and a few simple paintings of landscapes and people, being furnished with two sofas and a coffee table. A young man and woman were sitting on the sofa talking and laughing, while a middle-aged man who looked to be in his forties, with a pair of black-rimmed glasses, was frowning at a document on one side. A bulging briefcase and several papers cluttered the coffee table. Everyone in the room were completely oblivious to the entrance of Clark and Aunt Penny.","\n","^Just as Clark was about to say hello, an eerie chill burrowed into his body, sending a tingle through him; was there something in this living room that made him feel uncomfortable?","\n","ev","str","^Destroyed painting","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},"ev","str","^Strange bone decoration","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":20},["ev",{"^->":"12Inheritance.0.16.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-2","flg":18},{"s":["^It's just Clark's delusion...",{"->":"$r","var":true},null]}],{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"Destroyed_painting"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n",{"->":"bone"},{"#f":5}],"c-2":["ev",{"^->":"12Inheritance.0.c-2.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.16.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n",{"->":"Lawyers"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"Destroyed_painting":["^Walking up to the frame Clark sees that it is an oil painting of people, a couple and a child smiling at the camera. The painting looks to be some time old judging by the framing. But what is disturbing is that the child's face is smudged throughout with thick black paint, as if it doesn't want to be seen. The lady's face, on the other hand, has been painted with a light layer of white paint, making it impossible to get a good look at it either. The man's face was the only one that could be seen closely, and it was the face of a gentle, kind man. \"Is this some kind of unique art style?\" Clark thought to himself.","\n",{"->":"Lawyers"},{"#f":1}],"bone":["^This is a bone of a small animal with nails all over its head and red paint around its eye sockets - is this some kind of unique art style?","\n",{"->":"Lawyers"},{"#f":1}],"Lawyers":[["^The man in the suit interrupted Clark's thoughts and, as expected, he was the lawyer in charge of this distribution of the estate preparing to announce the exact contents of the will.","\n","^He introduced himself as Jarex and the couple as Quinn.","\n","^Leaving aside the legal complexities, the essence of the will is very simple - anyone on the will list who has lived in the house for three days will be entitled to an equal share of the estate.","\n","^\"It's that simple?\" Aunt Penny giggled.","\n","^The young couple, on the other hand, didn't react much, probably because they had already talked to the lawyer before.","\n","^At that moment the housekeeper came in and invited everyone to the dining room for dinner, at the end of which Clark went to the room where he would be living for the next three days.","\n","ev","str","^Looking around the room","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"room"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"room":[["^This on the ground floor is clean and immaculately tidied. It was wallpapered with flowers on a light green background. Apart from the bed, there is only a bedside table and a large wardrobe. The bed emitted a faint, musty smell characteristic of wood.","\n","ev","str","^Bringing the story back to the present","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"now"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"now":[["^.","\n","^Just as Clark was about to submit to sleep and slowly fall into a dreamy state, a strange voice reached his ears.","\n",["ev",{"^->":"now.0.4.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-0","flg":18},{"s":["^The sound of low footsteps actually came from underground. It was clearly on the ground floor, so why were there still human footsteps under the floor, was there a cellar? But if there was a cellar, who was walking around in it this late at night... With these lingering questions, Clark passed out.",{"->":"$r","var":true},null]}],{"c-0":["ev",{"^->":"now.0.c-0.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.4.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n",{"->":"Day1"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"Day1":[[["ev",{"^->":"Day1.0.0.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-0","flg":18},{"s":["^Day1",{"->":"$r","var":true},null]}],{"c-0":["ev",{"^->":"Day1.0.c-0.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.0.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n",{"->":"21Ask_the_housekeeper"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"21Ask_the_housekeeper":[["^Clark walked into the living room, and saw the housekeeper arranging the sofa.","\n",["ev",{"^->":"21Ask_the_housekeeper.0.2.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-0","flg":18},{"s":["^\"Can you tell me a little about why Mr. Marshall left such a strange will?\"",{"->":"$r","var":true},null]}],["ev",{"^->":"21Ask_the_housekeeper.0.3.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-1","flg":18},{"s":["^\"Is breakfast ready yet?\"",{"->":"$r","var":true},null]}],{"c-0":["ev",{"^->":"21Ask_the_housekeeper.0.c-0.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.2.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n",{"->":"22The_room_that_cant_be_opened"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["ev",{"^->":"21Ask_the_housekeeper.0.c-1.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.3.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n",{"->":"23Aunt_Pennys_terrible_cooking"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"22The_room_that_cant_be_opened":[["^\"I recall that Mr. Marshall left more detailed documents in his study to explain the will. The study is on the first floor, third from the left. The lock on the study door is a little jammed, so you will have to pull hard to get it open.\"","\n","^As the housekeeper said, the door to the study was pretty tough to open.","\n","ev","str","^Trying hard to open the door","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},"ev","str","^Leaving","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":20},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"221Dairy"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n",{"->":"23Aunt_Pennys_terrible_cooking"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"221Dairy":[["^An antique notebook sits on the table almost presenting itself for Clark to pick it up. Clark opened the notebook and found that it was written in a language he couldn't read.","\n","^A feeling of unease rose up from his heart.","\n","ev","str","^Leaving","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},"ev","str","^Continue to explore","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":20},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"23Aunt_Pennys_terrible_cooking"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ",{"->":"2211latch"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"2211latch":["^Clark noticed a dresser is not fully pushed up against the wall. He looked behind, spotting a wooden panel flesh with the wall and a latch on it. Clark tugged on the latch to open the supposed secret cabinet and looked into a pitch black void. At a quick glance to his right he catches a gaze with two mysterious glowing white dots. The two white dots seemingly stair right back at Clark with an intense sense of dread. Clark slams the cabinet just, scrambling out of the room.","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"Insanity"},1,"+",{"VAR=":"Insanity","re":true},"/ev",{"->":"23Aunt_Pennys_terrible_cooking"},{"#f":1}],"23Aunt_Pennys_terrible_cooking":[["^A bad stench enveloped the entire kitchen, making Clark forget everything but his desire to get out quickly. But a voice interrupted that thought, \"Come on honey, come try Aunt Penny's exclusive recipe.\"","\n",["ev",{"^->":"23Aunt_Pennys_terrible_cooking.0.2.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-0","flg":18},{"s":["^I'm not hungry",{"->":"$r","var":true},null]}],"ev","str","^It may not be as bad as it looks","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":20},{"c-0":["ev",{"^->":"23Aunt_Pennys_terrible_cooking.0.c-0.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.2.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n",{"->":"232Talking_Jareks"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n",{"->":"231Eat_your_breakfast"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"231Eat_your_breakfast":[["^The strange smell of the food was too much for Clark to handle, so he ran out.","\n","ev","str","^Forced to swallow","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},"ev","str","^Find a place to vomit","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":20},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"2311Stomach_pain"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n",{"->":"2312Rubbishbin"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"2311Stomach_pain":["^Clark spent half of the day at the toilet face constantly leaning over it, and didn't come out until the afternoon.","\n",{"->":"24rest_of_day"},{"#f":1}],"2312Rubbishbin":["^Clark rushed out, found a bin and spat out all the food in his mouth. As he was gasping for air, he noticed a large bucket of freshly opened red paint behind the bin, and paint-stained gloves... what exactly was it that required needing the gloves to do? Clark thought as he made his way back to the room.","\n",{"->":"232Talking_Jareks"},{"#f":1}],"232Talking_Jareks":[["^Clark noticed Jareks who was reading the newspaper, and asked him something about the inheritance.","\n",["ev",{"^->":"232Talking_Jareks.0.2.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str",{"CNT?":"221Dairy"},"/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-0","flg":19},{"s":["^I found Mr. Marshall's notebook.",{"->":"$r","var":true},null]}],["ev",{"^->":"232Talking_Jareks.0.3.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-1","flg":18},{"s":["^\"What kind of person was Mr. Marshall in his lifetime?\"",{"->":"$r","var":true},null]}],{"c-0":["ev",{"^->":"232Talking_Jareks.0.c-0.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.2.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n",{"->":"2332Discussing_witchcraft"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["ev",{"^->":"232Talking_Jareks.0.c-1.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.3.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n",{"->":"2321Marshalls_lifetime"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"2332Discussing_witchcraft":["^Mr. Jareks, with grave eyes, sighed and said, \"This is Mr. Marshall's diary, a diary which records all the efforts he has made since the death of his son.\" Efforts?\" \"Yes, he has been obsessed with witchcraft, and spent most of his remaining years trying to bring his son back from the dead\" Clark felt a bad chill run through him, as if he felt something and couldn't say it, as if a stone was weighing on his heart.","\n",{"->":"24rest_of_day"},{"#f":1}],"2321Marshalls_lifetime":["^\"It is not surprising that he could come up with such a strange will; he was himself a great lover of mischief.\"","\n","^There was an amused gleam in Mr. Jarek's eyes, as if he was recalling all the stories of Mr. Marshall's life.","\n",{"->":"24rest_of_day"},{"#f":1}],"24rest_of_day":["^The rest of the day passed in peace, and it was soon time for dinner.","\n",{"->":"25big_founding"},{"#f":1}],"25big_founding":["^At dinner time, the Quinn's told everyone they had made a \"big discovery\". The Quinn couple have promised to take everyone along to see the big discovery tomorrow.","\n",{"->":"26Mdinight"},{"#f":1}],"26Mdinight":["^At midnight, Clark was awakened by a nightmare. He looked through the window and saw a strange man dragging a large sack, slowly making his way to the woods behind the house. Out of fear, he dared not look any further and went back to bed, shivering","\n",{"->":"Day2"},{"#f":1}],"Day2":[[["ev",{"^->":"Day2.0.0.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-0","flg":18},{"s":["^Day2",{"->":"$r","var":true},null]}],{"c-0":["ev",{"^->":"Day2.0.c-0.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.0.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n","^It was a rough night for Clark, but as the birds began chirping their echoes could be heard all around the house, waking him up. Clark got up and prepared himself for a new day.","\n",{"->":"31missing_couple"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"31missing_couple":[["^Having familiarized himself with the estate yesterday, Clark quickly moved to the living room to rendezvous with the Quinn and the others. As he was approaching the area, he was amazed that he wasn't the first one to arrive. In fact, Clark was the last one to have arrived. Everyone else were patiently waiting, murmuring to themselves in separate corners of the room under an odd atmosphere. Clark awkwardly stood by the entrance and tried to get a sense of what's happening from each party in room, and finally he realized something.","\n","^The Quinn couple wasn't present, and all the others were discussing the disappearance of the couple on their own. Some even deducted a certain gloom outcome had taken place...","\n","ev","str","^Find the couple","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},"ev","str","^Walk into the room","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"32strange_room"},"\n",{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ",{"->":"33courtyard"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"33courtyard":["^Clark walked inside and tried to gather some information. Everyone in the room was shook and confused regarding the situation. As Clark glanced over the room and tried to start a conversation, he noticed a splash of dark red stain on the back of the courtyard, which was really hard to ignore looking from the window in the living room. That was probably why some people showed so much terror on their faces.","\n","^With Clark standing in the middle of the room, everyone finally noticed his presence and all seemingly turned toward him to share their confusions. ",{"->":"3330talk"},"\n",{"#f":1}],"3330talk":[["ev","str","^Talk to Leo, the housekeeper","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},"ev","str","^Talk to Penny, the Aunt","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":20},"ev","str","^Talk to Jarex, Marshall's lawyer","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-2","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"333leo"},"\n",{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ",{"->":"331penny"},"\n",{"#f":5}],"c-2":["^ ",{"->":"332jarex"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"333leo":[["^Clark talked to Leo. Leo did not seem to be affected by the scene in the courtyard, and told Clark confidently that it could just be the blood of some injured animals.","\n","^\"Mr. Clark, although I haven't worked here for a long time, but I have seen these stains quite a few times actually.\"","\n","^Clark tried to digest what Leo said, and slowly nodded his head. Apparently he was not convinced by it.","\n","^\"Now you might think it's eh... strange, Mr. Clark, but let me tell you something more. Since the day I work here, on each year there are a few days where I can find dead animals WITHOUT blood in them.\" Leo began to whisper into Clark's ear, probably thinking others might find his claim very funny. \"And these stains... were the blood from the dead animals. Sometimes it might be a rabbit, sometimes a bird. I never bother too much with the stains, it is the dried out corpse of animals in random corners of inside the estate is what frightens me.\"","\n","^Clark stood there for a moment, not sure how to respond to Leo.","\n","^\"O...kay. I will keep that in mind.\" Clark responded to Leo and stepped aside.","\n","ev","str","^Gather more information","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},"ev","str","^Tell everyone about last night","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"3330talk"},"\n",{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ",{"->":"3321tellEveryone"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"331penny":[["^Clark talked to Penny. Although Penny was confident with her cooking, she seemed very distress with the situation. She shakily said:","\n","^\"Clarky, oh lord. You are finally here.\"","\n","^\"Yes Aunt Penny, are you alright?\" Clark sensed something on Penny's mind.","\n","^\"No. Oh no I am not alright. Look at that in the back of the courtyard. That is blood. Bloodstains! Oh my god I cannot stay here any longer.\"","\n","^Penny was certainly shaking and did not want to stay in the estate any longer.","\n","^\"Listen Clarky,\" She came close to Clark and talked melancholically with a low voice, \"I think those must be the blood of Mr. Quinn and Mrs. Quinn. That's the only explanation on why they are not present here right now...\"","\n",["ev",{"^->":"331penny.0.12.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str",{"CNT?":"333leo"},"/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-0","flg":19},{"s":["^\"Calm down, it might just be some animal blood.\" Clark tried to ease out Aunt Penny. ",{"->":"$r","var":true},null]}],"ev","str","^Comfort Aunt Penny and gather more information","/str",{"CNT?":"333leo"},"!","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":21},["ev",{"^->":"331penny.0.21.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-2","flg":18},{"s":["^\"You are probably right, Aunt...\" Although Penny might be a bit unstable at the moment, but what she said did make some sense to Clark. ",{"->":"$r","var":true},null]}],{"c-0":["ev",{"^->":"331penny.0.c-0.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.12.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],{"->":"3321tellEveryone"},"\n",{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ Clark calmed Aunt Penny down and stepped aside. ",{"->":"3330talk"},"\n",{"#f":5}],"c-2":["ev",{"^->":"331penny.0.c-2.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.21.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],{"->":"3321tellEveryone"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"332jarex":[["^Clark talked to Jarex. Jarex, although worried, was offering Clark some of his thoughts regarding the stains.","\n","^\"I don't know what you have heard from the others, but this doesn't seem to be blood if I am being honest.\"","\n","^As per usual, Jarex talked with ease and gave a sense of beliefs in his words.","\n","ev","str","^Disagree with Jarex","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},"ev","str","^Agree with Jarex","/str",{"CNT?":"2312Rubbishbin"},"/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":21},{"c-0":["^ \"Well why not? It looks like blood to me.\" Clark disagreed with Jarex and stepped aside. ",{"->":"3321tellEveryone"},"\n",{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ \"Yes Jarex, I agree with you as I found something very interesting yesterday.\" Clark agreed with Jarex and stood up to tell everyone about his finding. ",{"->":"3322glove"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"3322glove":[["^Clark centered himself in the middle of the room for all to clearly hear, and told everyone that he found a pair of gloves yesterday, stained with red paint.","\n","^However, in a situation like this, such information was only adding more chaos to the room, people were starting to murmur again.","\n","^Clark then raised his voice even louder, and firmly said:","\n","^\"I believe those stains in the courtyard are also just from the red paint. As for Mr. and Mrs. Quinn, I will go to their room and see what I can find.\"","\n","^Clark actually did not want to look for them on his own, he just wanted to escape the room filled with distress. After all, he came here for fortune, not misfortune.","\n","ev","str","^Go to the Quinns' room","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"32strange_room"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"3321tellEveryone":[["^With the current situation, Clark decided to tell everyone in the room about what he saw last night, he made his way to the middle of the room and gathered everyones attention.","\n","^\"I woke up in the middle of the night due to a nightmare,\" Clark began, \"out of nowhere, I saw a figure dragging a huge sack inside the woods at the back.\"","\n","^The crowd remained silent, and Clark continued.","\n","^\"I was scared and hid myself under the bed sheet, but there are some weird things going on inside the woods, don't you all agree?\"","\n","^Clark felt that what he saw last night was related to the bloodstains and the missing couple.","\n","^\"Well, what say you then, shall we go and take a look?\" It was Leo that spoke first. Remaining in the living room would contribute nothing to the situation, and everyone knew that well.","\n","ev","str","^\"I agree, let's go.\"","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"333entrance"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"333entrance":[["^Clark and the others took a stroll into the woods. Although everyone was still confused and stressed from the current situation, a bit of fresh air from the gigantic red wood forests certainly helped ease some of the uneasy vibe within the group. Because the forest was so big, the group decided to split up and look for clues.","\n","^The stroll ended relatively quickly for Clark though, as he discovered something near a giant trunk of a red wood tree soon after.","\n","^\"Guys, come over here.\" Clark yelled, his voice echoed by the surrounding trees, but no one answered. He crouched down and carefully inspected the ground as he noticed something beneath the soil. Something was reflecting light.","\n","^\"This odd reflection here...\" Clark was speaking to himself as he put both his hands into the mud and tried to pave out the soil. And soon after, a metal door appeared. \"Voila! A hidden door!\"","\n","^Clark was amazed by the finding, but it was more of a comforting distraction as he did not know how was it related to both the blood stains or the Quinns.","\n","ev","str","^Lean close to the door","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"325block"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"325block":[["^There were voices coming from behind the door, vague but familiar. Clark pressed his ear up to the door to get a better grasp of what the voices were saying.","\n","^\"...Ma...\"","\n","^\"Haha.........Shall\"","\n","^Although Clark cannot quite comprehend what the voices were saying, but he was sure that they were human voices, and they sounded very very familiar.","\n","^\"Mr.... and Mrs. Quinn?\" Clark mumbled the words to himself as he finally recognized the voices of the distant conversation behind the door. He was sure that it was the Quinns behind the door.","\n","ev","str","^Try to find a way to open the door","/str",{"CNT?":"2321Marshalls_lifetime"},{"CNT?":"3211fake_couple"},"&&","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":21},"ev","str","^Try to listen to their conversations","/str",{"CNT?":"333leo"},"/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":21},"ev","str","^Try to open the door with force","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-2","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"326normalhe1"},"\n",{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ",{"->":"3261bigFinding"},"\n",{"#f":5}],"c-2":["^ ",{"->":"3262psychicbe"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"3262psychicbe":[["^Clark realized he did not have the key to open the door, so he took a few steps back and poised himself to charge down the door with pure force.","\n","^With only one firm kick, the door was burst open. The big metal doors smashed down on the ground forming a brief cloud of dirt. As the dust began to disperse at the entrance, Clark could not believe what he was in front of him.","\n","^Not too far away from the entrance, there was a naked body lying on an altar. The body was ripped open, with a solid cut that pierced through the abdomen, which he assumed could have been done with a dagger or sharpened knife. Clark took a long look at the face of the body, it appeared to be Mr. Quinn despite most of his facial features being displaced.","\n","^\"Mar...shall...arghhh...\" Next to Mr. Quinn's remaining corpse, a familiar voice was yelling. Clark turned his head toward the body, and out of the pure image of the scene, he fell aback and left sitting on the bloody floor. It was Mrs. Quinn's head, separated from her body and placed alone on a scale. Her mouth was gagged with shattered guts and she was making some terrifying noises.","\n","^Clark tried to regain his senses, but in this situation, he completely frozen, not even being able to move a muscle. Grasping the blood on the floor, he was praying that this was just another nightmare that he would wake up from at any moment. Coming to some senses he tried slapping his face, but to no avail, he did not wake up in a bed.","\n","ev","str","^Crawl back up","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"329psychicbe"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"329psychicbe":["^Clark tried desperately to crawl back up with the help of his survival instinct. He turned around and ran to the doorway as quickly as possible.","\n","^\"Ah, not so fast kid.\"","\n","^Out of nowhere, Clark stumbled upon a man dressed with a black robe.","\n","^\"You see, since you crashed into the ritual without my invitation, I can only surmise that this is a gift sent by the Worshipped. Perhaps you are the final puzzle piece to allowing me to reverse the death of my beloved son.\"","\n","^Clark heard what the man was saying, but at the same time was not able to comprehend what he had just heard. Just as he regained his composure, he tried to break way, but felt something pierce through his mouth from the back of his neck, and he slowly lost his consciousness.","\n","^But before he completely lost sight in front of him, he took a look at the man with the robe. In a brief moment Clark thought he saw the face beneath the robe somewhere around the estate, blacking out with an awed expression......","\n","^FIN.","\n","end",{"#f":1}],"3261bigFinding":[["^As Clark inched even closer to the door, the door suddenly opened. It was Mr. and Mrs. Quinn who were walking out from it.","\n","^\"Oh, Clark!\" Apparently Mr. Quinn was surprised by seeing Clark.","\n","^\"Mr. Quinn, and Mrs Quinn...\" Clark gave a sigh of relief after confirming they were the missing couple. \"We were all worried about you two when you had suddenly gone missing this morning.\"","\n","^\"Ah we are sorry about that,\" Mrs. Quinn responded, \"We need to confirm something. Remember what we told you about last night about our 'big discovery'? Have a look inside and see for yourself!\"","\n","ev","str","^Enter the door","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ Clark was confused, but he followed the couple through the metal door. ",{"->":"328witchcraft"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"328witchcraft":[["^Inside the door, there was a weird scent flowing all throughout the place. As Mr. Quinn lit up the candle, Clark could not believe what he was seeing. There were multiple counters that were engraved with weird symbols and writings. Containers and phials were all over the place, filled with weird colored liquids.","\n","^\"Is this... some witchery lab?\" Without a better choice of words, Clark asked the couple.","\n","^\"We are not sure. But it indeed looks to be something related to witchcraft rituals.\" Mr. Quinn continued, \"We wanted to see for ourselves before telling the others about this, because this is quite something... something terrifying.\"","\n","^\"If that's the case, we should definitely head back and tell the others.\" Clark sensed danger inside this hidden room and urged the couple to return to the estate.","\n","ev","str","^Return to the estate","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"329end"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"329end":["^Clark and the Quinn's returned to the estate. Everyone were sitting, waiting in the living room area as they welcomed them back. The others seemed to be relieved when seeing the Quinns safely returned to the estate, but soon turned into another form of distress as they learnt about the hidden room, the witchcraft props, and the mysterious ambience surrounding this estate.","\n","^The day was growing old with more information being discovered about the estate, and Clark retired straight into bed after having a long day.","\n",{"->":"Day3"},{"#f":1}],"326normalhe1":[["^Clark took a look around the door and spotted no key hole. He tried his luck and just pulled the door handle opening with ease. After peeking into the door, Clark carefully stepped inside and found something amazing.","\n","^Behind the door was a room filled with lavish furniture. It was a bit dark inside but it was filled with dimmed candlelights. From afar, where the voices were coming from, sat a gray-haired man on a huge couch. He was having a conversation with the Quinn couple.","\n","^The man and the couple seemed to be enjoying themselves with the conversation and did not see Clark, so he made his presence known:","\n","^\"Mr. and Mrs. Quinn?\"","\n","^The couple quickly turned around and were amazed to see Clark.","\n","^\"Oh, Clark! Wow! I totally did not expect to see you here.\" Mr. Quinn quickly stood up and welcomed Clark toward the couch area.","\n","^\"Yes uh... we were all quite worried about you see, because you guys just went missing...\" Clark continued, \"And I went looking for you, ending up here.\"","\n","^\"Right. We are sorry about that, but as you can see, we are indeed not missing but very lively here, with none other than Mr. Marshall himself.\"","\n","^Clark couldn't believe what he had just heard. \"Mr... Mr. Marshall?\"","\n","^\"Aye son, I am Marshall, the owner of this estate.\" The old man on the other couch said to Clark.","\n","ev","str","^Ask more about the situation","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"327he"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"327he":[["^\"Well, if you are Mr. Marshall, then what am I doing here? I thought I am here by your will to inherit this estate!\" Clark raised his voice a little bit, since this was pretty surreal that he was looking right at the man who he thought to be dead.","\n","^Mr. Marshall adjusted his body on the couch, slowly brushed his beard and finally said:","\n","^\"First of all, thank you for indulging me the pleasure to hold this trickery, and I am sorry that there will be no inheritance for you, or any other people that are in the estate right now. The truth is that every year, I put on a little game that I invite people to come to my house and play.\"","\n","^Mr. Marshall sipped some tea and continued. \"This year, I even prepared something special. Ah yes, a murder case. Mr eh... Quinn here is actually the famous \"Badguy\", Frederick Tate. And Mrs. Quinn is here is Mary Paul. Those names sound familiar to you?\"","\n","^\"Well, all I know is that they are actors.\" Clark was starting to comprehend the situation.","\n","^\"Exactly! And this year, I hired them to make up a murder case to have some fun inside the estate!\" Mr Marshall laughed by himself.","\n","^\"I am sorry Clark that you were let down by this, but it was nice to meet you.\" Mrs Quinn said to Clark playfully.","\n",["ev",{"^->":"327he.0.14.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-0","flg":18},{"s":["^\"So... this is just a show for you to enjoy?\" ",{"->":"$r","var":true},null]}],{"c-0":["ev",{"^->":"327he.0.c-0.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.14.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n","^\"Oh no, certainly not. This is a show for US to enjoy, don't you think son? I arrange this to not only to fulfill my old yet playful heart, but to also ease my guests from all the stress, problems, and pressure that they might feel in their everyday lives!\"","\n","^Clark laughed, almost a relieving laugh as he accepted the truth. There was no will, no inheritance, and no \"cases\". Although he was quite disappointed with the truth considering he was effectively jobless, but he appreciated Mr. Marshall's play, and decided to keep this as a secret to the others in the estate and finished enjoying the rest of his stay.","\n","^FIN.","\n","end",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"32strange_room":[["^Clark arrived at their room, and strangely the door remained unlocked and was cracked open ever so slightly. Clark knocked the door twice, perhaps for a sense of formality, and stepped inside the room in hope that the Quinns were in there. Unsurprisingly, the Quinn couple was not in their room, but Clark did notice something else.","\n","ev","str","^Investigate the suit case","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},"ev","str","^Investigate the weird shoes","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"321travel_case"},"\n",{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ",{"->":"322shoes"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"321travel_case":[["^Clark investigated the suit case that was left on the ground. Clark crouched down and wondered why there were briefcases were all over the place. When he inspected closely, he found out something strange.","\n","^On one briefcase, the name tag had \"Frederick Tate\" written on it. While the others had the name \"Mary Paul\". Indeed this was weird as none of the names included \"Quinn\" anywhere.","\n","ev","str","^Investigate the names","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"3211fake_couple"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"3211fake_couple":[["^Clark googled the names and found:","\n","^\"Frederick Tate(born November 24 1991) is a British actor that is known for his menacing charisma when portraying the antagonist, more commonly known as the 'Badguy'...\"","\n","^After scrolling down a bit, Clark also found that Mary Paul was also related to Frederick Tate:","\n","^\"Under the same acting agency, Mary Paul co-starred with Tate in various films and gained a reputation working together, some good and some bad.\"","\n","^Clark was confused, why were two actors' names on the Quinns' briefcases?","\n","ev","str","^Are the Quinns not the Quinns?","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"323breeze"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"323breeze":[["^As Clark was occupied by the his mixed thoughts, he felt a breeze that shivered his spine from underneath. There was a slight crack in the floor, leaving a small slit for the frozen stream to slip through. Clark shook at first, but soon after he realized that the cold stream meant something was beneath the floor. Clark regained his posture and put his fingers underneath the cracked floor. He felt a round object with polished texture. He put both hands under the floor to try to lift up the cracked wooden floor board, and managed to rip it out. What was under it though, surprised Clark, as the rounded polished object turned out to be a doorknob, and the door that laid on the surface of the floor was opened. That was the source of the cold breeze.","\n","ev","str","^Go beyond the door","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ Clark turned the knob of the door and opened it, heading inside. ",{"->":"324underground"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"324underground":[["^With a even stronger breeze coming right toward Clark's face, he struggled to keep his eyes open and discovered something magnificent.","\n","^The other side of this broken door was another world on its own. Although dark, Clark could feel the vastness of the area. Winds were blowing still but Clark was able to discover the area, and so he did.","\n","ev","str","^Investigate an odd aura","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},"ev","str","^Keep going","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ Clark kept going and noticed an odd aura was emitting in the corner. ",{"->":"3241latch"},"\n",{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ Clark kept going forward and soon he stumbled upon a door. ",{"->":"325block"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"3241latch":[["^Clark saw a latch that looked way out of place.","\n","ev","str","^Remember last time pulling the latch","/str",{"CNT?":"2211latch"},"/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":21},"ev","str","^Pull the latch","/str",{"CNT?":"2211latch"},"!","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":21},"ev","str","^Don't pull the latch and keep going","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-2","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"3242latch"},"\n",{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ",{"->":"32422open"},"\n",{"#f":5}],"c-2":["^ Clark disregarded the latch and kept on moving until he stumbled upon a door. ",{"->":"325block"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"3242latch":[["^Clark remembered last time he pulled the latch something terrifying happened.","\n","ev","str","^Pull the latch anyway","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},"ev","str","^Stray away and keep going","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"32422open"},"\n",{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ Clark kept going forward and soon he stumbled upon another door. ",{"->":"325block"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"32422open":[["^Clark opened the latch and saw a pair of eyes looking straight back at him. Staring for what felt like more than a minute, they seeming stared to swril leaving Clark with an even more uneasy feeling than he already had been feeling.","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"Insanity"},1,"+",{"VAR=":"Insanity","re":true},"/ev","ev","str","^Turn around and keep going","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ As Clark was horrified by the scene, he quickly turned around and kept going. Not soon after, he calmed himself down and stumbled upon a door. ",{"->":"325block"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"322shoes":[["^Clark noticed the couples' shoes were still in the room. How odd.","\n",["ev",{"^->":"322shoes.0.2.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-0","flg":18},{"s":["^Surely they won't go anywhere without their shoes on...  ",{"->":"$r","var":true},null]}],{"c-0":["ev",{"^->":"322shoes.0.c-0.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.2.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],{"->":"323breeze"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"Day3":[["^Clark was greeted by the morning sun, which didn't seem to warm up the room despite the way it illuminated the space. He tossed and turned, thinking about the events of the night before. The blood, the secret room… What could this all mean? Something is not adding up.","\n","^But laying around in bed isn’t going to solve anything, is it?","\n","ev","str","^Get up and get ready for the day","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"4200getready"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"4200getready":[["^He changed into his clothes and set out for the day. He walked along the corridor, eyes scanning everything and anything in hopes of finding some kind of clue.","\n","^“Mr. Clark? Is something wrong,” a voice asked behind him. He jumped and turned to find a girl staring back at him.","\n","^“Huh?”","\n","^“You were staring at that painting for quite a bit.”","\n","^“ Oh? Was I? I think I might’ve just been deep in thought,” Clark gave a nervous chuckle, placing his hand over his chest as if it would help to slow down his thumping heart. He had never seen her before, but she was wearing something similar to what Leo usually wears, so he assumed that she was one of the housekeepers.","\n","^He looked up at the painting. It was a portrait of an older man with quite the stereotypical appearance: lean, white hair and beard, a stern look on his face that paired along with the wrinkles on his frown lines. He wore an expensive-looking suit and lots of accessories befitting his financial status, and yet there seemed to be a dark atmosphere around him despite the shine from his accessories. He guessed that it was Marshall.","\n","ev","str","^\"May I ask you something?\"","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"4300questions"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"4300questions":[["^She stood still behind him, almost unmoving.","\n","^\"What would you like to know?\"","\n","ev","str","^\"What kind of person was Mr.Marshall\"","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},"ev","str","^\"What do you know about witchcraft in the house?\"","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":20},"ev","str","^\"How did you get behind me?\"","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-2","flg":20},"ev","str","^\"Nothing else\"","/str",{"CNT?":"4320answer"},"/ev",{"*":".^.c-3","flg":21},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"4310answer"},"\n",{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ",{"->":"4320answer"},"\n",{"#f":5}],"c-2":["^ ",{"->":"4330answer"},"\n",{"#f":5}],"c-3":["^ ",{"->":"4400choice"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"4310answer":[["^“Mr Marshal was a respectable man. A gracious one too. He treated us well, but was never really around. He also seemed to be distant at times…” She shook her head. “ I’m sorry, I don’t know him that well. Not a lot of people do as a matter of fact. At least, not any deeper than what he shows”.","\n","ev","str","^Ah, I see","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"4300questions"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"4320answer":[["^“Witchcraft?” Suddenly, her composure broke, and her giggles echoed along the corridor. “I’m sorry, but I don’t know anything about witchcraft here”.","\n","^“Although,” she looked around and leaned in. “It might be in your best interest to look around the library”, she whispered, “third case, third shelf, third book from the right”. She stepped back in her original spot and  her smile disappeared from her face, as if whatever possessed her at the moment had left her body.","\n","ev","str","^Ah... I see","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"4300questions"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"4330answer":[["^\"She tilted her head to the side? “ I was behind you the entire time. Maybe you were just too focused on the painting?”","\n","^“I wasn’t focused on the painting, though”","\n","^“Well...\"","\n","ev","str","^...","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"4300questions"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"4400choice":[["^Clark watched her walk down the hallway quietly.","\n","^“Mr. Clark!”","\n","^Clark turned to see Leo coming from the other end of the hall.","\n","ev","str","^Follow the girl","/str",{"VAR?":"Insanity"},2,">=","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":21},"ev","str","^Wait for Leo","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"4122insanity"},"\n",{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ",{"->":"4500Leo"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"4500Leo":[["^Clark watched Leo walk as he approached him down the hall, each footstep echoing loudly in the empty air.","\n","^“Leo” Clark greeted him casually.","\n","^“Ah Mr. Clark. I have been looking for you all morning. Didn’t see you at breakfast so I thought I’d come fetch ya.”","\n","^“Breakfast? Oh god, what time is it?”","\n","^“It is half past noon”","\n","^“Half past noon?!” Clark swore he woke up not too long ago. Has he been standing here for hours? He looked at the painting again and felt a shiver down his spine. The eyes… looked a little too real. The way the color blended into the whites of his eye-","\n","^“Mr. Clark?”","\n","^Clark snapped back into reality. “Ah, sorry about that. I seem to be out of it recently.”","\n","^“Don’t you worry about it. Aye, with all that’s been happening the past couple of days, it’s bound to shake ya in yalls boots,” Leo says. “So… what would you like to do for your breakfast?”","\n","^“I think I’ll skip it for today”. The unsettling feeling in his stomach seemed to rid of his appetite for the day.","\n","ev","str","^Ask about the library","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"4600asklibrary"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"4600asklibrary":[["^“Oh the library?” Leo asked surprisingly.","\n","^“Why are you so surprised?”","\n","^“No reason, really. It’s just that no one likes to go to that place. Gives a lot of people the creeps.” Leo shuddered. “Would ya look at that,” he exclaimed, “seems as though even talking about it ain’t no good”.","\n","^“Well, I would still like to take a look”","\n","^“You like reading?”","\n","^“... Maybe. Every now and then”","\n","^Leo gives Clark a hard look. “Alright. It’s up the stairs and a couple doors down to the left. You’ll know which one it is. It’s gonna be them big doors”.","\n","ev","str","^Head to the library","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"4700atlibrary"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"4700atlibrary":[["^Clark thanked him and walked towards the stairs, footsteps filling the void.","\n","^He climbed up the wooden stairs in the main hall, and turned left. Just like Leo had instructed, there were a pair of big doors further down the hall. Clark stood in front of the door. It was quite big, bigger than the other doors.The door demanded attention with its ornate carvings and details. However, the carvings of ivy and snakes did not seem welcoming for those passing by. Even Clark felt a bit intimidated. Not because of the door, but because of what Leo had said before.","\n","ev","str","^Open the door","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"4800inlibrary"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"4800inlibrary":[["^With a gulp, Clark turned the brass doorknobs and pushed. Surprisingly enough, the door swung open with just a push. The room was dark, with only a stained glass window to illuminate the room with its colors. A cold breeze swept through the room.","\n","^Clark stepped into the room and thought, shit.","\n","^The room was filled with bookcases, expanding across the walls either side of him. How is he supposed to know which third case it is? Left? Right?","\n","ev","str","^Right","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},"ev","str","^Left","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"4810right"},"\n",{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ",{"->":"4820left"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"4810right":[["^He turned to the right.","\n","^Third case…","\n","^Third shelf…","\n","^Third book…","\n","^He picked up the dusty book. The cover read “Pride and Prejudice”.","\n","^“What the..” Clark mumbled, “Who knew this was the old man’s taste?”","\n","ev","str","^Return","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":[{"->":"4800inlibrary"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"4820left":[["^He turned to the left","\n","^Third case…","\n","^Third shelf…","\n","^Third book…","\n","^He picked up the dusty book. The cover read “Persuasion”.","\n","^“What the..” Clark mumbled, “Who knew this was the old man’s taste?”","\n","^Just then the book slipped out of its covers and onto the ground.","\n","^He picked up the book and examined the cover. There was no title. Rather, it seemed more like a diary almost. It was leather bound, with the edges of the pages worn out.","\n","ev","str","^Open the book","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"4900openbook"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"4900openbook":[["^Clark flipped through the pages. The contents were written in ink with elegant penmanship. If it weren't for the graphic diagrams and ominous symbols, one could say that the pages were beautiful.  On the sides were little writings, something that you would see in a student’s notes. He flipped the next page.","\n","^Subject 1.","\n","^Species: Rat","\n","^Time of dea -","\n","^Clark closed the book. He didn’t want to look any further. He realized what he had seen. It was a record of different test subjects.  For witchcraft...","\n","^He had to leave. He felt his empty stomach churn. And the colors of the stained glass windows were not helping.","\n","ev","str","^Leave","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"4110exitlibrary"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"4110exitlibrary":[["^He stumbled out of the library and was grateful for the musty hallway air. He took a deep breath, trying to control the growing acidity in his stomach. Maybe a glass of water would help.","\n","ev","str","^go to the kitchen","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"4111kitchen"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"4111kitchen":[["^He walked into a lively kitchen, with Auntie Penny cooking up something for dinner. She was humming a little tune as she swayed side to side to the beat.","\n","^“Oh Clarky, you’re just in time for dinner! Oh come sit, you must be hungry”","\n","^She motioned for Clark to sit as she started plating the food. It smelled… interesting.","\n","ev","str","^Sit and Eat","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},"ev","str","^Make an excuse","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"4112death"},"\n",{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ",{"->":"4113excuse"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"4112death":["^Clark sat down and started eating. It was actually decent at first, even though he didn’t know exactly what he was eating.","\n","^Suddenly, Clark felt his stomach churn. Pain starts erupting from the bottom of his stomach and he starts to feel fire burning in his stomach lining. He grasped his stomach in hopes that the pressure would ease the pain, but he felt something rising in his throat. It blocked his throat, forcing him to spit out the food and blood. He covered his mouth with his hand, trying to stop the bright red blood from dripping from his mouth. He felt hot. The pain was subsiding, or was he just losing consciousness? Aunt Penny screamed, but even that sounded distant. The world spun, and suddenly, he couldn’t see.","\n","^Later autopsy reports indicate that someone had poisoned the food, but Aunt Penny persisted that she would never try to kill her own nephew. Despite pleads and the evidence stacking against Penny with being awarded the contents of the will, she was later prosecuted and pleaded guilty on a charge of murder of the first degree with a 15 year sentence.","\n","^In the back of the court room an old man was seen tipping his hat to some of those attending the case as a big grin covered his face while Penny was being escorted out of the court room.","\n","^FIN.","\n","end",{"#f":1}],"4113excuse":[["^“Thank you, but I had a late lunch so I’m not too hungry,” Clark lied.","\n","^“Oh is that so?” She turned to take a look. “But you look so thin, Clarky, and so pale”.","\n","^He touched his face, and noticed that he did seem a little thinner. “Oh, I’m sure it’s all the walking I’ve been doing recently”","\n","^“Oh is that so? Well, I guess it is good to get some exercise in” She turned back to her stove. “Did you need anything, sweetie?”","\n","^Clark thought about eating, but the smell seemed to rid of his appetite once more.","\n","^“No, I think I’m good, I was just wandering around”","\n","ev","str","^Leave","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"4114hallway"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"4114hallway":[["^He left the kitchen and went back into the hall. The sun was setting, casting long and dark shadows in the hallway. Deep in thought, he started wandering around the mansion.","\n","^Clark felt something tickle the back of his neck, as if someone was staring at him. He looked back. He was alone in this empty hallway. And yet, Clark felt very nervous. He continued to walk down the hall. Suddenly, he heard steps behind him. It followed his pace, step by step.","\n","ev","str","^Walk","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"4115steps"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"4115steps":[["^Step.","\n","^Step.","\n","^Step.","\n","ev","str","^Look behind","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"4116stranger"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"4116stranger":[["^Clark whirled around to face whatever was behind him. At the other end of the hall, he saw a silhouette. The sun just about set, and the silhouette was hidden in the shadows.","\n","ev","str","^RUN","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"4117chase"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"4117chase":[["^Clark ran as fast he could. His feet hit the ground, the shock of the impact burning up to his knees, but he didn’t care. He ran, the musty mansion air in his face, and the clothes sticking onto his frame. He couldn’t look back… could he?","\n","ev","str","^Look back","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},"ev","str","^Keep running","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"4118death"},"\n",{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ",{"->":"4119running"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"4118death":["^He looked back, the shadow silhouette hot on his trail, a lot closer than he had anticipated. The silhouette was fast. Why was it so fast?","\n","^He tried to run faster, but his foot got caught on a wrinkle of the rug. He fell on his arm, and he gasped from the pain of the impact. His arm was numb, and tried to get up back on his feet, but his legs gave out beneath him. He saw a shadow loom behind him. He tried to look back and see the face of the silhouette as a last attempt of desperation, but the world turned black.","\n","^And somewhere in the house, the clock struck midnight.","\n","^FIN.","\n","end",{"#f":1}],"4119running":[["^No, he had to keep going. He ran, but he felt his legs become weak. He knew he couldn’t run much longer.","\n","ev","str","^Hide in a room","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},"ev","str","^Keep going","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"4121end"},"\n",{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ",{"->":"4120death"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"4120death":["^He kept running. He didn’t even know if those rooms were locked and he didn’t know where this person behind him was either.","\n","^Suddenly, he felt the rug slip beneath him. He fell on his arm, and he gasped from the pain of the impact. His arm was numb, and tried to get up back on his feet, but his legs gave out beneath him. He saw a shadow loom behind him. He tried to look back and see the face of the silhouette as a last attempt of desperation, but the world turned black.","\n","^And somewhere in the house, the clock struck midnight","\n","^FIN.","\n","end",{"#f":1}],"4121end":[["^He swerved to the side, grabbing onto the doorknob, and praying that it’ll unlock.","\n","^Click","\n","^The door opened. He rushed inside, closing the door behind him. His legs gave out, and he collapsed onto the ground. He gasped for air through his hands, in hopes that it would help muffle the sounds.","\n","^The room was silent and dark. He only heard his own breathing. His heartbeat rung in his ear.","\n","^Step. Step. Step. Step.","\n","^He heard slow footsteps beyond the door.","\n","^Step. Step. Step","\n","^It stopped at the door.","\n","^The room was silent, but his heartbeat seemed to beat louder and louder.","\n","^And somewhere in the mansion, the clock struck midnight","\n","ev","str","^Day 4","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"Day4"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"4122insanity":["^“Hey, wait up!”","\n","^The girl continued to walk and Clark tried to run, but he was… running in place?","\n","^Suddenly the walls started to distort. Faces appeared from the swirls of the flowered wallpapers. The faces stretched and stretched in agony, as if someone was pulling on the skins of their faces. Clark tried to move, but arms rose from the carpets and pulled him in. He was losing control.","\n","^“Wait!” He cried “Help me!”","\n","^But the girl only continued to walk until she melded into the wallpapers. The walls started to melt and cave in, pooling around his legs as he struggled to be free the grasps of the hands. Was he dying? Was he hallucinating? Or was he going crazy? The sound of metal clanging that started afar, seemed to have become loud enough for it to be right next to his ear. He tried to block his ears, but it was no use.","\n","^He slumped into the melting ground, feeling his face become one with the paint of agonizing faces.","\n","^And somewhere in the distance, he heard the clock strike midnight.","\n","^FIN.","\n","end",{"#f":1}],"Day4":[["^As Clark awoke, leaning against the door he looked around the room and saw nothing out of the norm. He inspected his body top down in a full body mirror just to the left of him and saw nothing wrong.","\n","^He slow crept back to the door cracking it open ever so slight as not to make a single sound. Peeking his head out and looking done both ends of the hall he did not notice anything out of place.","\n","ev","str","^Wait in room a little while longer","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},"ev","str","^Go check out the common areas for the other guest","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"Epilogue11"},"\n",{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ",{"->":"Epilogue21"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"Epilogue11":[["^Clark decided to wait in the room for a couple hours more in hopes that what ever was lurking in the hallway last night has forgot about him.","\n","^Clark tip toes down the hall not hearing the faintest of noise, not even chirping of the birds. He makes his way to the living area only to find that Aunt Penny is passed out on the couch, but she isn't snoring or making a sound.","\n","^Running over to check in on her, shaking her violently to wake up you get no response.","\n","^\"Aunt Penny?\" Clark Murmurs while he tries to listen and feel for a heart beat.","\n","^Gasping you start to tear a little, before trying to find help, still not wanting to make too much noise.","\n","ev","str","^Look for Leo","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"Epilogue12"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"Epilogue12":[["^Clark scampered about the kitchen only to find Leo hunched over the sink. Hands covering his gasping face you have no idea what has happened to all the guest and other who were living at the estate. Could they be all dead?","\n","^It doesn't make any sense as the 3 days have passed, but who could have killed all the remaining guest? That figure that was roaming the halls last night? Coming to the realization that the potential predator is still about, Clark rushes to the front door and swings it open only to be greeted by a man wearing a fedora and trench coat. Clark in total shock is left frozen as he thinks back to the portrait he spent hours staring at yesterday only to piece together that the man in front of him was the same one that was in the painting... Marshall.","\n","^\"Hello young man, I see you have found your friends and loved ones around the home, we can't have you leave this place unattended, after all you have won it!\"","\n","^Suddenly everything goes dark as you have been covered with a sack by someone from behind.","\n","ev","str","^What is this place?","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},{"c-0":["^ ",{"->":"Epilogue13"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"Epilogue13":["^The sack that was covering Clark is removed and he is slapped awake.","\n","^\"Welcome Darling!\" Shoots Marshall with what appears to be the Quinns joining him as his side. \"You see you have been pretty nosey, in fact you have uncovered the most about me compared to the many guest that I have had spend a night at this estate. Well son, you will be a noble sacrifice to the rebirth of my son and I thank you for your hard work and efforts on being the first to make it all three nights!\"","\n","^Clarke looks down at his arms and legs and sees that he is complete chained to a metal chair.","\n","^\"I promise this will only be a little painful\" as Mr. Quinn bows before Mr.s Marshall holding out a dagger which he unsheathes and sticks right into Clark's chest carving out the heart. Marshall exclaims to Clark in his dying breaths, \"Rest easy my child, has a new one will be born in your shadow!\"","\n","^Clark complete blacks out never to return awaken again.","\n","^FIN.","\n","end",{"#f":1}],"Epilogue21":[["^Clark decided to bolt down the hall and abruptly stopped as you almost rammed right into Aunt Penny. Screaming almost instantly, \"WE NEED TO GET OUT OF HERE NOW!\" gasping for breath, \"I think Mr. Marshall is a serial killer and that the will is fake. A man chased me throughout the hall last night and I think would have killed me if I hadn't gotten to safety in on of the rooms.","\n","^Aunt Penny with a look of utter shock and surprise says, \"This place is very terrifying and I don't want to get caught in deep water with this Mr. Marshall figure.\"","\n","^Both Clark and Aunt Penny bolt for the door and head down the road into town.","\n","^\"I don't know if we get the authorities involved or not?\" Clark says while he notices a punch of missing people poster littered at the bus stop the two are passing by.","\n","ev","str","^Seeing the poster contacting the authorities seems like the best bet","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},"ev","str","^Deciding not to as you don't want to deal with that estate or Mr. Marshall ever again","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":20},{"c-0":[{"->":"Epilogue31"},"\n",{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ",{"->":"Epilogue41"},"\n",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"Epilogue31":["^Since there were no cell phones allowed at the manage the pair seek out a pay phone to contact the local police telling them about the estate and what both went through during their stay.","\n","^\"Many groups of people go missing and this could be were the lead we are looking for!\" says the operator with glee.","\n","^Upon arrival of a squad car, Clark and Aunt Penny hop in and direct the officers toward where the mansion was, only to drive down the very road they came running up to find it leading to a empty field with nothing but cattle.","\n","^\"Is this some kind of joke?\" one of the cops angrily say.","\n","^Gasping at the sight Clarke say, \"That isn' possible we just came from the estate which was in this very spot.\"","\n","^With no hint of the state ever existing in that spot the cop car turns around and heads back into down, with a defeated and very paranoid Clark sobbing in the back seat.","\n","end",{"#f":1}],"Epilogue41":["^Clark and Aunt Penny hug good buy and go their separate ways in hopes they never runner into the people associated with that estate ever again, not saying a word about it ever again.","\n","end",{"#f":1}],"global decl":["ev",0,{"VAR=":"Insanity"},"/ev","end",null],"#f":1}],"listDefs":{}};